sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K165095
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Gli1 bs + LexA bs + mCYC + Zif268-HIV repressor (mCherryx2 tagged) on pRS303
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Szymanski

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K165031
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: mCYC promoter plus LexA binding sites
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a composite part containing the minimal promoter mCYC preceded by multiple consecutive binding sites for the LexA binding domain.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Aaron Glieberman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Composite part was taken via PCR from a synthetic plasmid containing the sequence. The plasmid came from Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It was necessary to design primers for use in PCR to remove this part from its host plasmid and transfer it to a standard Biobrick vector

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K165002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The kozak sequence acts as a eukaryotic RBS. It is cloned directly between a promoter and coding region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Szymanski

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Sin3
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a transcriptional repression domain. It can be fused to many DNA-binding domains to create synthetic transcriptional repressors. We have used it upstream of DNA binding domains.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Szymanski
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: From the yeast genome, via Caroline Ajo-Franklin.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mCherry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the mCherry fluorescent protein, yeast-codon optimized and biobricked in the silver lab BioFusion standard for use in fusion proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Szymanski

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mCherry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the mCherry fluorescent protein, yeast-codon optimized and biobricked in the silver lab BioFusion standard for use in fusion proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Szymanski

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: NLS+Term
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: SV40 nuclear localization sequence + ADH1 transcription terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The SV40 nuclear localization sequence can be added to any coding region to have it expressed in the nucleus in yeast. This is useful for building synthetic transcription factors. In this part, it is ligated to the ADH1 transcription terminator for convenient cloning to the end of coding sequences.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Szymanski
